Considering the most basic case of Scenario 1 ; where there is complete compliance throughout the duration of mask enforcement , and the absence of time-limited immunity , Figure 3 shows the cases where mask wearing were to be enforced ( a ) on the day the first case of COVID-19 was detected in Singapore ; ( b ) after a 50 days delay ; ( c ) after a 100 days delay ; and ( d ) not enforced at all .
